245
00:20:18,400 --> 00:20:24,960
can't get that what Brian Eno calls scenius. 
Brian Eno has this great word that he uses,  

246
00:20:24,960 --> 00:20:30,240
scenius is the genius that comes when you have 
a group together. Scenius is the collective  

247
00:20:30,240 --> 00:20:35,920
idea of genius and I think that's something that's 
really magical that I've experienced in my career,  

248
00:20:35,920 --> 00:20:40,000
but usually in smaller groups. 
It's hard to do with a giant group.

249
00:20:40,720 --> 00:20:44,960
I love this metaphor of The Beatles as 
the way most people describe this is  

