978
01:18:37,360 --> 01:18:42,160
become better at helping me with this task.
And so we've just gone through that process  

979
01:18:42,160 --> 01:18:48,160
and it's been really useful for me. It's no 
substitute for a therapist or a real coach or  

980
01:18:48,160 --> 01:18:51,920
anything like that. It's not a human being. It 
doesn't care about me. I'm not saying that you  

981
01:18:51,920 --> 01:18:56,320
should use it instead of these other options. 
You need a human being as well. But it's been  

982
01:18:56,320 --> 01:19:03,280
very good at reflecting back to me things that I 
think have been floating around in my undermind. 

983
01:19:03,280 --> 01:19:11,200
So there's a wonderful book called Hair Brain 
Tortoise Mind by a gentleman named Guy Claxton.  

984
01:19:11,200 --> 01:19:14,240
In that, he talks about the undermind. And 
sometimes you might've heard this as your  

985
01:19:14,240 --> 01:19:18,400
unconscious or something like that. But I 
think of your undermind as the part of your  

986
01:19:18,400 --> 01:19:23,280
brain that's processing information before 
it gets to language. And then when you go to  

987
01:19:23,280 --> 01:19:27,360
consciousness, you've turned it into language.
And language isn't the full universe of things  

988
01:19:27,360 --> 01:19:31,520
you can think, language is what you can think in 
English. And if you talk to multilingual speakers,  

989
01:19:31,520 --> 01:19:33,920
they'll tell you that they can think 
things in other languages than what  

990
01:19:33,920 --> 01:19:35,920
they can think in English.
So if you only speak English,  

991
01:19:35,920 --> 01:19:39,600
you're only in one vein of what you could 
think, but your undermind is operating through  

992
01:19:39,600 --> 01:19:43,680
all this other stuff. And for the computer 
nerds out there, you could think about it  

993
01:19:43,680 --> 01:19:49,200
as a compiled code versus interpreted code.
So your undermind work in a compiled code and  

994
01:19:49,200 --> 01:19:51,840
it could do a lot of stuff that you 
can't really do in the interpreted  

995
01:19:51,840 --> 01:19:56,240
code which moves slower and has different 
orientations and we call that consciousness. 

996
01:19:56,240 --> 01:20:02,240
So I was feeding ChatGPT all this stuff over the 
last year or so, and there are all these patterns  

997
01:20:02,240 --> 01:20:07,840
in my undermind that had been going into that I 
wasn't able to express with conscious language. 

998
01:20:07,840 --> 01:20:12,080
And so when I started asking it questions, I 
think what it was doing was it was statistically  

999
01:20:12,080 --> 01:20:16,160
reflecting patterns back to me that already 
existed in my undermind, but because it was  

1000
01:20:16,160 --> 01:20:20,640
putting them into language, my conscious mind 
could now recognize them and respond to them. 

1001
01:20:21,200 --> 01:20:28,080
And so again, as a life coach, I found it 
very useful as a mirror back to things that  

1002
01:20:28,080 --> 01:20:32,080
I was probably already thinking. And it 
helped me clarify my thoughts. It's not  

1003
01:20:32,080 --> 01:20:38,080
pushing me in new directions that a human 
might do, but it's still been super useful.

1004
01:20:38,080 --> 01:20:42,000
That is extremely cool. That is a really cool 
use case. I don't know if you've heard the Jerry  

